ed in pairs as it forages in the tree tops for mistletoe, fruits and berries, but may also be seen on tracks and roadsides seeking grit or small invertebrates. In southern Central America, this species is replaced at higher altitudes by its close relative, the very similar ruddy pigeon, Patagioenas subvinacea. They can be distinguished by the slower, more complex \"song\" of the short-billed pigeon. References Stiles, F. Gary & Skutch, Alexander Frank (1989): A guide to the birds of Costa Rica. Comistock, Ithaca. ISBN 0-8014-9600-4 External links Short-billed pigeon photo; Article (AOCR) Short-billed pigeon photo gallery VIREO Short-billed pigeon videos on the Internet Bird Collection", "shortSummary": "The short-billed pigeon (Patagioenas nigrirostris) is a largish pigeon which breeds from southern Mexico south to northwestern Colombia. It…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Short-billed_Pigeon.jpg/960px-Short-billed_Pigeon.jpg", "order": "Columbiformes", "family": "Columbidae", "genus": "Patagioenas", "species": "Patagioenas nigrirostris", "orderCn": "鸽形目", "familyCn": "鸠鸽科", "genusCn": "新大陆鸽属", "speciesCn": "短嘴鸽", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-patagioenas", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-patagioenas-nigrirostris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-patagioenas", "species": "taxonomy-species-patagioenas-nigrirostris"}, "expandable": true, "x": -928.45, "y": -6.59, "z": 29.75}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-patagioenas", "name": "新大陆鸽属", "latinName": "Patagioenas", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "新大陆鸽属（Patagioenas）是图谱中的分类